The United States switches todaylight saving time on Sunday, April 5, when clocks will beturned ahead one hour at 0200 in all time zones.    The states of Arizona and Hawaii and parts of Indiana,including Indianapolis, remain on standard time by localchoice.    Congress voted last year to move the start of daylight timefrom the last Sunday in April to the first Sunday in April. Thereturn to standard time remains the last Sunday in October(October 25 this year).    Canada also switches to daylight time on Sunday. Reuter&#3;